Spain Daybook: Zapatero Backs Rubalcaba, Keeps Control of Socialist Party

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-05-30T06:34:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/spain-daybook-zapatero-backs-rubalcaba-keeps-control-of-socialist-party.html
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero endorsed his deputy Alfredo Perez Rubalcaba’s
bid to become the Socialist candidate at the general election
scheduled for next year and won the support of regional party
leaders to continue at the head of his party.  WHAT TO WATCH: *Bond markets may be active after the premier
shut down a power struggle within his party which had threatened
to trigger an early general election.  ECONOMY: * Spain ’s National Statistics Institute publishes its
first estimate of May inflation at 9 a.m. CET. *European Central
Bank Executive Board member Jose Manuel Gonzalez-Paramo said
Spain must finish reforms making its labor market more flexible
to win back investors’ confidence, La Vanguardia reported.  EQUITIES:  * Gas Natural SDG SA (GAS)  said it will issue a maximum of 32.9 million
new shares in a bonus capital increase and shareholders will get
one new share for every 28 existing shares.  MARKETS:
*The IBEX 35 Index rose 0.6 percent to 10,261.20.
*The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs
widened to 234 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net  